<div class="d-t">
  <div class="s">Why Three Peptides Beat One</div>
  <p>Running BPC-157 alone gives you excellent angiogenesis and growth factor signaling. But you miss the structural remodeling from TB-500 and the collagen-building, gene-modulating effects of GHK-Cu. Stacking all three creates a repair environment where blood supply, cellular scaffolding, and raw building materials are all present simultaneously.</p>
</div>

<!-- ========== DOSING ========== -->
<hr class="sep">
<h2>Dosing Protocols</h2>

<p>The standard KLOW protocol reflects the most commonly cited dosing ranges in peptide research and clinical reports. Individual adjustments depend on injury type, severity, and body weight. Always work with a healthcare provider when determining your protocol.</p>

<h3>Standard KLOW Protocol</h3>

<table class="tbl">
<thead><tr><th>Peptide</th><th>Dose</th><th>Frequency</th><th>Duration</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr><td><strong>BPC-157</strong></td><td>250&ndash;500 mcg</td><td>Twice daily (AM/PM)</td><td>4&ndash;8 weeks</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>TB-500</strong></td><td>2.5 mg</td><td>Twice weekly</td><td>6&ndash;8 weeks</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>GHK-Cu</strong></td><td>2&ndash;4 mg</td><td>Daily</td><td>6&ndash;8 weeks</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<h3>Injury-Specific Modifications</h3>

